angles in the architecture. Actually, everything in the house as well as the
house itself is designed entirely of straight lines and angles. The floor, in
keeping with this design scheme, has no rug but relies on strips of hardwood
interspaced with seemingly random segments of gold and silver, but as you study
it more intensely, you see an intricate mathematical design in the placement of
each board, segment of gold or silver, and even the direction of grain and hue
of stain in the wood. It obviously took intense planning to lay out the floor.
The furniture is placed with care so as not to disturb the mathematical design,
and so, enhances it.
~
