#6961
Maison de Laura Annette~
As you enter Laura Annette's house you are immediately thrown back by its
elegance and beauty, even for this village! Nothing you have ever seen compares
to this, except for one other house in this village. The walls are adorned with
beautiful tapestries and jewel encrusted, gold framed portraits, one of them
looking quite like Audrey Renee-Maree, the ceiling, one huge painting depicting
a story of times long ago, the floors bare but polished so highly that you can
see your reflection as if there were a second you beneath you. The
chaise-longue, sofas, short tables, and lighting fixtures are all of the most
elegant nature. You could spend hours just looking around the house at all the
beauty without becoming bored.
~
