#6962
Maison de Claude~
You have entered the home of a hopeless art collector. There are expensive works
of art everywhere, from walls covered in tapestries with paintings hanging over
them and each other to the dramatically artistic furniture with sculptures of
animals, heads, people, plants, and some other stuff that has no meaning laying
on top, in front, behind, and under it, to elaborate lighting fixtures with
glass, emerald, diamond and ruby menagerie hanging from them. Each item would
look absolutely beautiful if it were not for all the other things all around it.
As it is, the total enormity of numbers and the disarray with which the artwork
is placed makes it more of an eyesore.
~
