Maison de Jean-Pierre~
You have entered Jean-Pierre's house. Portraits of what you deem to be past
relatives through many generations form the focal point of his house. Each one
is expertly painted and in an elaborate gold frame. The furniture is made of
dark, dramatically sculptured wood, overlaid in strategic places to add to its
aesthetic nature without being overly dramatic. If it weren't for the extreme
extravagance of the village, you would consider this a dramatic absurdity of the
use of wealth and an attempt to throw it in your face, but taking the great
wealth of the city into consideration, it seems actually to be more conservative
than you would expect.
~
